msContents.summary: A catechism or brief theological summary of Christian doctrines and liturgy in Arabic, arranged in question and answer format; the first subject is "Fī wujūd Allāh". A table of contents in a different hand was added at the end (p. [215]).

supportDesc.extent: 214 paginated leaves, 1 leaf : 232 x 163 (160 x 105) mm, bound to 232 x 170 mm

layoutDesc.layout: 19 long lines with catchwords every verso.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in naskh in black ink; pointed.

binding.p: Bound in modern cardboard painted with narrow blue stripes and red snowflake or floral patterns with flap; red leather spine and fore-edge hinge covers; blue paper pastedowns.

origin.p: Item is undated, but likely copied in the 19th century.
